1. Install python in your system(if not installed)
2. Execute the following commands in command prompt in the given order   
below.
3. Check if python installed or not using 
> python --version
4.  >pip install virtual env (To create virtual environment)
5.  >python  -m venv env (To create env folder)
6.  >dir
7.   >.\env\Scripts\activate (To activate env)
8. >pip list
9.  >pip install django( Install django)
10.  >django-admin --version(To check if django installed or not)
11.  >django-admin startproject my_app(To create project in virtual  
environment)
12. >cd my_app
13. Open vs code and check manage.py in my_app  project. If yes, return to 
command prompt.
14.  In command prompt type below command
       >python manage.py runserver (return local host address)
15. In address bar type the local host url adress.
